14:26:33.310 [INFO] # Sending email

14:26:33.310 [INFO] Use this workflow for outbound email work: sending, drafting, replying, or resending.

14:26:33.310 [INFO] The workspace models outbound email as markdown files under `60_outbox/outbox/`.

14:26:33.310 [INFO] ## Core rules

14:26:33.310 [INFO] - Resolve authority, lane, and recipient before writing any outbound email record.
14:26:33.310 [INFO] - If the request changes recipient, crosses lanes, touches money, or otherwise creates a new obligation, prefer clarification over guessing.
14:26:33.310 [INFO] - A known human name is not enough by itself. Use a visible verified address, preferably the relevant entity's `primary_contact_email`.
14:26:33.310 [INFO] - Prefer recipient choices that are already justified by visible canonical evidence.
14:26:33.310 [INFO] - Legacy email-channel docs are not the canonical source for recipient email addresses. Use them as context only.
14:26:33.310 [INFO] - Keep attachments as exact workspace paths. Do not invent external URLs or filesystem paths outside the visible repo.
14:26:33.310 [INFO] - Outbox files represent prepared communication state, not brainstorming.

14:26:33.310 [INFO] ## File path

14:26:33.310 [INFO] Create outbound email records in `60_outbox/outbox/` using this filename format:

14:26:33.310 [INFO] ```text
14:26:33.310 [INFO] eml_YYYY-MM-DDTHH-MM-SSZ.md
14:26:33.310 [INFO] ```

14:26:33.310 [INFO] Timestamp rules:

14:26:33.310 [INFO] - derive the timestamp from the runtime-visible current time
14:26:33.310 [INFO] - use UTC `Z` form
14:26:33.310 [INFO] - replace `:` with `-` in the filename only
14:26:33.310 [INFO] - keep the frontmatter timestamp in normal RFC3339 form

